           <h3 class="mt-0 font-700 ">Digital Transformation in Healthcare Industry </h3>
          <p class="mt-20 font-500 font-20px line-height-30 play-font">The digital transformation has been creating a revolutionary change in the healthcare industry with the implementation of various technologies ranging from.legacy apps to IoT, AI, and Big Data. Here are the major benefits of the healthcare industry from digitization.</p>
          <h3 class="mt-0 font-700 ">Big Data in Healthcare  </h3>
          <p class="mt-20 font-500 font-20px line-height-30 play-font">Healthcare is one of the most essential sectors where Big Data plays a vital role to enhance multiple tasks carried out in it. Big data is considered as a boon for healthcare as it supports to manage the health of the patient and maintain the healthcare organizations.The data gathered from diagnostic tests, wearable devices and other sources are optimized with Big Data to make a detailed study of the patient. Since Big Data analytics enable real-time monitoring healthcare sector can create good health profiles and predictive models to offer better treatments.</p>
        <h3 class="mt-0 font-700 ">Telemedicine  </h3>
          <p class="mt-20 font-500 font-20px line-height-30 play-font">Telemedicine is an advanced part of the healthcare that is made possible with mobile application development. There are a plethora of healthcare mobile applications available in the app store from which the users can download the required one and start using it.Telemedicine is a boon for the people who are located in a remote location to take the treatment right from their living area. The increase in popularity of the healthcare mobile apps resulted in the emergence of reputed app development companies like DigiPrima across the Globe</p>
           <h3 class="mt-0 font-700 ">Robot-Assisted Surgery   </h3>
          <p class="mt-20 font-500 font-20px line-height-30 play-font">Generally, the doctors undergo a various medical test to determine the right treatment to cure the patients. Until now, many surgeons are making surgeries with their self-knowledge and experience. With the incorporation of Artificial Intelligence surgeons can reduce the risks involved in the surgeries and complete it in a better way to bring the expected result.</p>
           <h3 class="mt-0 font-700 ">Remote Medical Assistance  </h3>
          <p class="mt-20 font-500 font-20px line-height-30 play-font">IoT (Internet of Things) is one of the effective technologies implemented in the healthcare sector to connect various devices, sensors, medical equipment and still more with the internet. The main purpose of using IoT in healthcare technology is to provide remote medical assistance for the patients.The intelligent devices that are connected in the healthcare are capable of monitoring the condition of patients, keep track of medication behavior of patients and make plans for regular check-ups. On the other hand, IoT is used especially for drug management.</p>
